_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-18t14:02:13z","updated_at":"2013-12-18t14:02:13z","body":"with the anonymous upload there is no need for the uploader to create an account.\r\n\r\nfor you as the user how wants to receive an anonymous upload will create a folder, share it and let people know to drop files there - this can be seen as the activation part.\r\n\r\nin other words this feature request can be implemented with existing core features.\r\nanything else would be a perfect match for an 3rdparty app."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30851002","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6488#issuecomment-30851002","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6488","id":30851002,"user":{"login":"pvince81","id":277525,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f89d7c394e6dcdf87a91c75ac3b2ccbe8.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81","html_url":"https://github.com/pvince81","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pvince81/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-18t15:35:46z","updated_at":"2013-12-18t15:35:46z","body":"maybe @mikevbh doesn't want all people (externaluser1, externaluser2) to upload files into the same publicly shared folder, but that every one user gets a different one. else this means externaluser2 would also get access to the files uploaded by externaluser1.\r\n\r\nlike you said it could be implemented as a separate app. that app could work that way:\r\n1) provide a public url for anonymous users\r\n2) when that url is opened, auto-create a subdir for that user (with a generated id)\r\n3) share that subdir with public link and allow upload (using the ocs share api)\r\n4) redirect the user to that public link's page\r\n5) user can then upload files\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30853469","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6488#issuecomment-30853469","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6488","id":30853469,"user":{"login":"mikevbh","id":6214408,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/04c8833a5759328aebd93cae7138050e?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f8671762694c0f2da90b20652ea5b1b7e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"04c8833a5759328aebd93cae7138050e","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh","html_url":"https://github.com/mikevbh","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikevbh/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-12-18t16:01:15z","updated_at":"2013-12-18t16:01:15z","body":"@pvince81 have read my mind, i also forgot to mention that i always set an expiration date to all my shared links (for security reasons), meaning if the receiver is not on time, or if the user needs to upload something else later, there is no way to send me the files using my owncloud, unless i share the link again of course."}]